WINDOW COVERINGS FOR THE BUILD 😬🪟👀🙌🏽
- 
Having lived with taped up garbage bags in the girls’ rooms for the last while, getting window coverings ready for move-in was a must for me + I was feeling v limited with the Canadian options. I had no idea about all the amazing, fully custom offerings from @blindstogo, but when I went into their showroom their team was able to deliver on my exact vision for our kitchen + bedrooms! Bonus that they’re a Canadian company, made in Canada + offer a lifetime warranty!
- 
I went with roman shades in a neutral palette (if you’re not familiar, imagine if a blind + a drape had a baby lol). They are all fully motorized which is such a treat (+ necessary bc of the height of some of our windows) + I was able to get blackout for all the bedrooms despite the light materials. 
-
I’m going for relaxed elegance with timeless fabrics + textures and I cannot WAIT for you guys to see these installed soon! Are we feeling the vibe?! xx

WHY I LOVE UNLACQUERED BRASS ✨🤍
-
It’s no secret I love unlacquered brass + have it all over our build (hardware, door knobs, faucets, lighting), but here are some reasons I especially love it in our kitchen: 
✔️ it’s about as timeless a material as you can choose! It’s been around forever + always will be imo.

✔️ it matures + ages beautifully! I intend to let ours patina + show the character, but you can also shine or polish it. 

✔️ it has natural antibacterial properties (making it perfect in a kitchen) 

✔️ it’s not a manipulated finish, which means aside from the natural patina, it will match all other unlacquered brass regardless where you buy from. I sourced our hardware from a few places and it still looks seamless. Try to order all at once if you want it to change at the same speed, though!
